<subSubSection id="07AD654AFFCAFF43FF25FA4FFDE9F98F" pageId="5" pageNumber="586" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="4F0836C1FFCAFF43FF25FA4FFDE9F98F" blockId="5.[151,1437,1022,2021]" pageId="5" pageNumber="586">
<emphasis id="7DC3EAD3FFCAFF43FF25FA4FFEA5FA56" bold="true" box="[199,324,1490,1516]" pageId="5" pageNumber="586">Diagnosis:</emphasis>
A species of 
<taxonomicName id="88B74D42FFCAFF43FE37FA4EFDB2FA56" authorityName="G. W. Muller" authorityYear="1898" box="[469,595,1491,1516]" class="Ostracoda" family="Cyprididae" genus="Zonocypris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Podocopida" pageId="5" pageNumber="586" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="7DC3EAD3FFCAFF43FE37FA4EFDB2FA56" box="[469,595,1491,1516]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="586">Zonocypris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with a small, sub-rectangular to sub-ovate carapace in lateral view, with the typical ornamentation of concentric ribs almost horizontal in the central and ventral areas; intercostal areas smooth and slightly thicker than the ribs.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="07AD654AFFCAFF40FF25F9A3FE08FF0B" lastPageId="6" lastPageNumber="587" pageId="5" pageNumber="586" type="description">
<paragraph id="4F0836C1FFCAFF43FF25F9A3FBDDF8B7" blockId="5.[151,1437,1022,2021]" pageId="5" pageNumber="586">
<emphasis id="7DC3EAD3FFCAFF43FF25F9A3FEBAF9E2" bold="true" box="[199,347,1598,1624]" pageId="5" pageNumber="586">Description:</emphasis>
Small carapace, sub-rectangular to sub-ovate in lateral view. Carapace ovoid, in dorsal and ventral views, posteriorly broadened, anteriorly acuminate. LV larger than RV, uniformly overlapping it along all margins, except in the ventral margin. Greatest height at mid-length in females, in front of middle in males. Greatest length below mid-height. Greatest width in posterior third. Dorsal margin convex, ventral margin almost straight; anterior margin sub-rounded, posterior margin truncated and projected downwards. Sexual dimorphism pronounced, with females higher, less elongated, more inflated and dorsally more convex than males.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="4F0836C1FFCAFF43FF25F88AFD7EF85F" blockId="5.[151,1437,1022,2021]" pageId="5" pageNumber="586">
Concentric ribs parallel to margins on carapace periphery. In central region of carapace, ribs more triangular shape, being almost horizontal in ventral zone. Intercostal areas smooth and slightly thicker than ribs. On ribs, or adjacent to them, simple normal pore canals (
<typeStatus id="900C8863FFCAFF43FD74F8C2FD29F8C3" box="[662,712,1887,1913]" pageId="5" pageNumber="586">type</typeStatus>
A’ of 
<bibRefCitation id="2B264B30FFCAFF43FCEEF8C2FC11F8C3" author="Puri, H. S. &amp; Dickau, B. E." box="[780,1008,1887,1913]" pageId="5" pageNumber="586" pagination="353 - 367" refId="ref8154" refString="Puri, H. S. &amp; Dickau, B. E. (1969) Use of normal pores in taxonomy of Ostracoda. Transactions Gulf Coast Association of Geological Societies, 19, 353 - 367." type="journal article" year="1969">Puri &amp; Dickau 1969</bibRefCitation>
and A1 of 
<bibRefCitation id="2B264B30FFCAFF43FB8CF8C2FA8AF8C3" author="Danielopol, D. L. &amp; Cabral, M. C. &amp; Lord, A. &amp; Carbonel, P. &amp; Gross, M. &amp; Stoica, M. &amp; Humphreys, W. F. &amp; Namiotko, T. &amp; Mohr, E. &amp; Kulkoyluodlu, O. &amp; Piller, W. &amp; Nunes, T." box="[1134,1387,1887,1913]" pageId="5" pageNumber="586" pagination="1 - 64" refId="ref6709" refString="Danielopol, D. L., Cabral, M. C., Lord, A., Carbonel, P., Gross, M., Stoica, M., Humphreys, W. F., Namiotko, T., Mohr, E., Kulkoyluodlu, O., Piller, W. &amp; Nunes, T. (2018) Sieve-type pore canals in the Timiriaseviina - A contribution to the comparative morphology and the systematics of Limnocytheridae (Ostracoda). Zootaxa, 4495 (1), 1 - 64. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4495.1.1" type="journal article" year="2018">
Danielopol 
<emphasis id="7DC3EAD3FFCAFF43FB10F8C2FAC2F8C3" box="[1266,1315,1887,1913]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="586">et al</emphasis>
. 2018
</bibRefCitation>
) are abundant, some of which seemingly with marginal lip (
<typeStatus id="900C8863FFCAFF43FCE0F81EFCD5F827" box="[770,820,1923,1949]" pageId="5" pageNumber="586">type</typeStatus>
A” of 
<bibRefCitation id="2B264B30FFCAFF43FC62F81EFB82F827" author="Puri, H. S. &amp; Dickau, B. E." box="[896,1123,1923,1949]" pageId="5" pageNumber="586" pagination="353 - 367" refId="ref8154" refString="Puri, H. S. &amp; Dickau, B. E. (1969) Use of normal pores in taxonomy of Ostracoda. Transactions Gulf Coast Association of Geological Societies, 19, 353 - 367." type="journal article" year="1969">Puri &amp; Dickau 1969</bibRefCitation>
and A2 of 
<bibRefCitation id="2B264B30FFCAFF43FB02F81EFF32F87B" author="Danielopol, D. L. &amp; Cabral, M. C. &amp; Lord, A. &amp; Carbonel, P. &amp; Gross, M. &amp; Stoica, M. &amp; Humphreys, W. F. &amp; Namiotko, T. &amp; Mohr, E. &amp; Kulkoyluodlu, O. &amp; Piller, W. &amp; Nunes, T." pageId="5" pageNumber="586" pagination="1 - 64" refId="ref6709" refString="Danielopol, D. L., Cabral, M. C., Lord, A., Carbonel, P., Gross, M., Stoica, M., Humphreys, W. F., Namiotko, T., Mohr, E., Kulkoyluodlu, O., Piller, W. &amp; Nunes, T. (2018) Sieve-type pore canals in the Timiriaseviina - A contribution to the comparative morphology and the systematics of Limnocytheridae (Ostracoda). Zootaxa, 4495 (1), 1 - 64. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4495.1.1" type="journal article" year="2018">
Danielopol 
<emphasis id="7DC3EAD3FFCAFF43FA86F81EFA7CF827" box="[1380,1437,1923,1949]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="586">et al.</emphasis>
2018
</bibRefCitation>
), bad preservation of specimens not allowing for more detailed description (
<figureCitation id="D78C2A44FFCAFF43FBDEF83AFB76F87B" box="[1084,1175,1959,1985]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1837,1861]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,525,1814]" captionTargetId="figure-165@6.[151,1436,525,1814]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 3. Zonocypris dorsoconvexa sp. nov. (A–D), LMA-00333, holotype, male carapace, (A) general ventral view, (B) general dorsal view, (C) general right view, (D) ventral view, anterior part, marginal pore canals; (E) LMA-00306, paratype 1, female carapace, general left view; (F–H) LMA-00334, paratype 2, juvenile carapace, (F) general right view, (G) general left view, (H) ventral view, anterior part, simple normal pore canals (types A’ and A”? of Puri &amp; Dickau 1969 and A1 and A2? of Danielopol et al. 2018)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6598169" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6598169/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="586">Fig. 3H</figureCitation>
). Marginal pore canals also present, more densely arranged (
<figureCitation id="D78C2A44FFCAFF43FDDAF856FD72F85F" box="[568,659,1995,2021]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1837,1861]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,525,1814]" captionTargetId="figure-165@6.[151,1436,525,1814]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 3. Zonocypris dorsoconvexa sp. nov. (A–D), LMA-00333, holotype, male carapace, (A) general ventral view, (B) general dorsal view, (C) general right view, (D) ventral view, anterior part, marginal pore canals; (E) LMA-00306, paratype 1, female carapace, general left view; (F–H) LMA-00334, paratype 2, juvenile carapace, (F) general right view, (G) general left view, (H) ventral view, anterior part, simple normal pore canals (types A’ and A”? of Puri &amp; Dickau 1969 and A1 and A2? of Danielopol et al. 2018)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6598169" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6598169/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="586">Fig. 3D</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="4F0836C1FFC9FF40FF25FF0AFE08FF0B" blockId="6.[151,1436,151,502]" box="[199,489,151,177]" pageId="6" pageNumber="587">Internal features not seen.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="07AD654AFFC9FF40FF25FF26FF04FE4C" pageId="6" pageNumber="587" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="4F0836C1FFC9FF40FF25FF26FDAEFE17" blockId="6.[151,1436,151,502]" pageId="6" pageNumber="587">
<emphasis id="7DC3EAD3FFC9FF40FF25FF26FED5FF6F" bold="true" box="[199,308,187,213]" pageId="6" pageNumber="587">Remarks</emphasis>
: This species differs from the previous Z 
<emphasis id="7DC3EAD3FFC9FF40FCEEFF26FC03FF6F" box="[780,994,187,213]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="587">
onocypris 
<taxonomicName id="88B74D42FFC9FF40FC61FF26FC03FF6F" authority="Piovesan &amp; Melo &amp; Cabral &amp; Guzmán, 2022" authorityName="Piovesan &amp; Melo &amp; Cabral &amp; Guzmán" authorityYear="2022" box="[899,994,187,213]" class="Ostracoda" family="Cyprididae" genus="Zonocypris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Podocopida" pageId="6" pageNumber="587" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="berthoui" status="sp. nov.">berthoui</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
<emphasis id="7DC3EAD3FFC9FF40FC08FF26FBA4FF6F" bold="true" box="[1002,1093,187,213]" pageId="6" pageNumber="587">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="66F057A8FFC9FF40FC08FF26FBA4FF6F" box="[1002,1093,187,213]" pageId="6" pageNumber="587" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
in general outline, mainly the dorsal one, less robust ribs and the posterior position of greatest width. 
<taxonomicName id="88B74D42FFC9FF40FC4BFF42FB28FF43" authority="Piovesan &amp; Melo &amp; Cabral &amp; Guzmán, 2022" authorityName="Piovesan &amp; Melo &amp; Cabral &amp; Guzmán" authorityYear="2022" box="[937,1225,223,249]" class="Ostracoda" family="Cyprididae" genus="Zonocypris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Podocopida" pageId="6" pageNumber="587" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dorsoconvexa" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="7DC3EAD3FFC9FF40FC4BFF42FB28FF43" box="[937,1225,223,249]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="587">Zonocypris dorsoconvexa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="7DC3EAD3FFC9FF40FB2CFF42FAC7FF43" bold="true" box="[1230,1318,223,249]" pageId="6" pageNumber="587">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="66F057A8FFC9FF40FB2CFF42FAC7FF43" box="[1230,1318,223,249]" pageId="6" pageNumber="587" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
resembles 
<taxonomicName id="88B74D42FFC9FF40FF75FE9EFEB0FEA7" box="[151,337,259,285]" class="Ostracoda" family="Cyprididae" genus="Zonocypris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Podocopida" pageId="6" pageNumber="587" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="undefined-1">
<emphasis id="7DC3EAD3FFC9FF40FF75FE9EFEF4FEA6" box="[151,277,259,284]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="587">Zonocypris</emphasis>
sp. 1
</taxonomicName>
from the Early Aptian of 
<collectingCountry id="37A07651FFC9FF40FD91FE9EFD33FEA7" box="[627,722,259,285]" name="Portugal" pageId="6" pageNumber="587">Portugal</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="2B264B30FFC9FF40FD03FE9EFC8EFEA7" author="Cabral, M. C." box="[737,879,258,285]" pageId="6" pageNumber="587" refId="ref6186" refString="Cabral, M. C. (1995) Ostracodos do Cretacico inferior do Algarve e da regiao de Lisboa: sistematica, biostratigrafia, aspectos paleoecologicos e paleobiogeograficos. PhD thesis (unpublished), Universidade de Lisboa, Lisboa, 442 pp." type="book" year="1995">Cabral 1995</bibRefCitation>
), but the latter has a straighter ventral margin and a more marked posterior end; the ornamentation is also slightly different with the ribs more inclined in the ventral area. The species 
<taxonomicName id="88B74D42FFC9FF40FEBDFED6FDE7FEDF" box="[351,518,331,357]" class="Ostracoda" family="Cyprididae" genus="Zonocypris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Podocopida" pageId="6" pageNumber="587" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis id="7DC3EAD3FFC9FF40FEBDFED6FE3CFEDE" box="[351,477,331,356]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="587">Zonocypris</emphasis>
sp.
</taxonomicName>
, recorded from the Early Cretaceous from 
<collectingCountry id="37A07651FFC9FF40FC0AFED6FBB6FEDF" box="[1000,1111,331,357]" name="Argentina" pageId="6" pageNumber="587">Argentina</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="2B264B30FFC9FF40FB84FED6FA81FEDF" author="Carignano, A. P. &amp; Paredes, J. M. &amp; Olazabal, S. X. &amp; Valle, M. N." box="[1126,1376,331,357]" pageId="6" pageNumber="587" pagination="206 - 220" refId="ref6431" refString="Carignano, A. P., Paredes, J. M., Olazabal, S. X. &amp; Valle, M. N. (2017) Ostracoda (Crustacea) from the Pozo D- 129 Formation (upper Barremian? - Aptian), Golfo San Jorge basin, Patagonia, Argentina: Taxonomic descriptions, palaeoenvironments and palaeogeographical implications. Cretaceous Research, 78, 206 - 220 https: // doi. org / 10.1016 / j. cretres. 2017.06.015" type="journal article" year="2017">
Carignano 
<emphasis id="7DC3EAD3FFC9FF40FB06FED6FAFCFEDF" box="[1252,1309,331,357]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="587">et al.</emphasis>
2017
</bibRefCitation>
), differs from 
<taxonomicName id="88B74D42FFC9FF40FEE6FEF2FDC4FE33" authority="Piovesan &amp; Melo &amp; Cabral &amp; Guzmán, 2022" authorityName="Piovesan &amp; Melo &amp; Cabral &amp; Guzmán" authorityYear="2022" box="[260,549,367,393]" class="Ostracoda" family="Cyprididae" genus="Zonocypris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Podocopida" pageId="6" pageNumber="587" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dorsoconvexa" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="7DC3EAD3FFC9FF40FEE6FEF2FDC4FE33" box="[260,549,367,393]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="587">Zonocypris dorsoconvexa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="7DC3EAD3FFC9FF40FDC8FEF2FD62FE33" bold="true" box="[554,643,367,393]" pageId="6" pageNumber="587">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="66F057A8FFC9FF40FDC8FEF2FD62FE33" box="[554,643,367,393]" pageId="6" pageNumber="587" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
in the more rounded anterior margin, and position of the greatest width in the posterior quarter of the carapace.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="4F0836C1FFC9FF40FF25FE2BFF04FE4C" blockId="6.[151,1436,151,502]" pageId="6" pageNumber="587">
<emphasis id="7DC3EAD3FFC9FF40FF25FE2BFEBDFE6A" bold="true" box="[199,348,438,464]" pageId="6" pageNumber="587">Occurrence:</emphasis>
Late Aptian, Crato Formation, Araripe Basin, Crato Municipality, 
<collectingRegion id="8D73F823FFC9FF40FB9CFE2AFAE9FE6B" box="[1150,1288,439,465]" country="Brazil" name="Ceara" pageId="6" pageNumber="587">Ceará State</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry id="37A07651FFC9FF40FAFBFE2AFABCFE6B" box="[1305,1373,439,465]" name="Brazil" pageId="6" pageNumber="587">Brazil</collectingCountry>
(this study).
</paragraph>
